    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nRelated: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/27855\n\nCurrently the message window is a floating window, which can be confusing when the cursor is switched to an underlying split window covered by the message floating window (the cursor is visible but not inside the message window):\n\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/76ef51e3-968d-4a41-b216-b66299c42337\n\n`minimal.lua`:\n\n```lua\nrequire('vim._extui').enable({})\n\nprint([[\nThis\nis\na\nmulti\nline\nmessage\nfor\ntest\npurposes\n]])\n```\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nOpen message windows in a split, or add an option of type `vim.api.keyset.win_config` to control window options of the message window. ",
