            "body": "> Do you think this would be solved by automatically closing the window when the user moves away from it?\n\nGiving my 2 cents here: I would prefer this, specially when there's no way to navigate back to the `:messages` window via `<C-W>j` (and so it seems that in order to close the window I need to use my mouse to place the cursor back and press `q`).\n\nPerhaps a flexible solution would be having `close_events` like https://neovim.io/doc/user/lsp.html#vim.lsp.util.open_floating_preview.Opts.",
