        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> regular split seems worth trying, since 'splitkeep' gives it the same advantages as a floating overlay?\n\nIf there is a single window yes; with horizontal splits, not quite.\n\n> One of the reasons that I suggest using split window for messages is that I compare the new message window with the existing and established cmdwin, quickfix window, and preview window -- they are all small split windows used to show some special contents, so I think maybe it will be nice to maintain some consistency for the messages window, or at least allow some customization option to open the message window in a split.\n\nThe more-prompt is already established as a floating grid, so in that sense using a floating window more closely mimics the status-quo, which is why I chose it. Can of course make it configurable but I think we want to keep the float default.\n\n#33831 closes the float again when leaving it. Keeping in mind further configurability for later.",
